Return the mean and the HPDI/credible intervals of the parameters of the model

Source: R/bpc_get_parameters.R
get_parameters.Rd

Return a data frame with the mean and with high and low 95% hpd interval or credible interval for all parameters of the model

get_parameters(
  bpc_object,
  params = NULL,
  HPDI = TRUE,
  credMass = 0.95,
  n_eff = FALSE,
  Rhat = FALSE,
  keep_par_name = T
)

Arguments

bpc_object

a bpc object
params

a vector with the parameters to use. If null then all will be present
HPDI

should return the HPDI or the credible intervals. Default is returning the HPDI
credMass

probability mass for the summary stats
n_eff

Should include the number of effective samples in the df
Rhat

Should include the Rhat in the df
keep_par_name

keep the parameter name e.g. lambdaGraff instead of Graff. Default to T. Only valid for lambda, so we can have better ranks

Value

a data frame containing a column with the parameters, a column with mean and two columns with higher and lower intervals

Examples

# \donttest{
m<-bpc(data = tennis_agresti,
player0 = 'player0',
player1 = 'player1',
result_column = 'y',
model_type = 'bt',
solve_ties = 'none')

#> Running MCMC with 4 parallel chains...
#> 
#> Chain 1 finished in 1.7 seconds.
#> Chain 2 finished in 1.8 seconds.
#> Chain 3 finished in 1.8 seconds.
#> Chain 4 finished in 1.7 seconds.
#> 
#> All 4 chains finished successfully.
#> Mean chain execution time: 1.7 seconds.
#> Total execution time: 2.0 seconds.
hpdi<-get_parameters(m)
print(hpdi)
